org.eng.aisp.util

Class BalancedLabeledWindowIterable<ITEM extends ILabeledDataWindow<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.aisp.util.BalancedLabeledWindowIterable<ITEM>
  • Type Parameters:
    ITEM -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<ITEM>, ISizedIterable<ITEM>

    public class BalancedLabeledWindowIterable<ITEM extends ILabeledDataWindow<?>>
extends Object
implements ISizedIterable<ITEM>
    Provides label value balancing in an iterable of labeled data windows. Data may be balanced in 1 of 3 ways:
    1. down sampled - the minimum count of all label values is used as the count for all labels values produced. Label values that occur more frequently are randomly excluded to reduce their number to the minimum count.
    2. up sampled - the maximum count of all label values is used as the count for all labels values produced. Label values that occur less frequently are duplicated to the maximum count. A balanced copy across each window is attempted.
    3. by count per label value.
    Author:
    DavidWood

    • Constructor Detail

      • BalancedLabeledWindowIterable

        public BalancedLabeledWindowIterable(Iterable<ITEM> iterable,
                                     String labelName,
                                     boolean upCopy)
        Parameters:
        iterable - labeled data windows to restrict to be balanced.
        labelName - the label name for which the label values will be balanced.
        upCopy - if true, then up copy samples as needed so that each label value has a number of samples equal to the maximum number of samples for any label value. If false, then down sample randomly to bring the number of samples per label to the maximum number of samples for any label value.

      • BalancedLabeledWindowIterable

        public BalancedLabeledWindowIterable(Iterable<ITEM> iterable,
                                     String labelName,
                                     int samplesPerLabelValue)
        Create the iterable to select the requested number of samples per label value. Samples will be up-sampled (copied) and down-sampled (randomly) to meet the requested number of samples per label value.
        Parameters:
        iterable - labeled data windows to restrict to be balanced.
        labelName - the label name for which the label values will be balanced.
        samplesPerLabelValue - the number of samples produced for each label value assigned to the given label name.
